## What problem is your app playground trying to solve and what inspired you to solve it?
*(200 words max)*

In 2018, Kerala flooded. It was the worst in a century. The Malayalam film '2018' later showed the world what that looked like, but I didn't need a movie. I was fourteen, in Chennai, calling home to Thalassery while my mother tried reaching relatives across Kannur. Calls kept dropping. People we knew were stranded for days with no power and no signal. Nobody could look up whether the water was still rising or what to do if someone got hurt.

Then in 2024, the Wayanad landslides hit one district away from my hometown. Chooralmala, Mundakkai. Places people in Kannur drive to for weekends. Gone overnight. Rescuers dug through mud with bare hands. Again, people had phones, but those phones had nothing useful on them.

We Keralites show up for each other. Neighbours become rescue teams. Fishermen become first responders. But showing up isn't enough when you don't know what to do.

That is why I built Revive. It is a completely offline survival guide. 505 techniques, 15 emergency triage trees, 1,875 step-by-step instructions. No server calls, no internet needed. It puts first-responder knowledge directly onto the device people are already holding when the grid goes down.

